# Database & ORM Standards

## Prisma (Node API)

### Client Singleton

```typescript
// db.ts — single shared instance, never create new PrismaClient in modules
import { PrismaClient } from '@prisma/client';

const db = new PrismaClient({
  log: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development' ? ['query'] : [],
});

export default db;
```

### Migration Workflow

```bash
# Development — evolve schema iteratively
npx prisma db push

# Production — generate and apply tracked migration
npx prisma migrate dev --name describe_change
npx prisma migrate deploy   # CI/CD deploy step

# Seed initial data
npx prisma db seed
```

### Query Patterns

```typescript
// ✅ Typed, safe queries
const tenders = await db.tender.findMany({
  where: { status: 'ACTIVE', dt: { gte: startDate } },
  select: { id: true, title: true, budget: true },
  orderBy: { createdAt: 'desc' },
  take: pageSize,
  skip: (page - 1) * pageSize,
});

// ✅ Transactions for multi-step writes
await db.$transaction([
  db.tender.update({ where: { id }, data: { status: 'AWARDED' } }),
  db.auditLog.create({ data: { action: 'AWARD', entityId: id, userId } }),
]);

// ⚠️  Raw SQL — only for full-text search, never for writes
const results = await db.$queryRawUnsafe(
  `SELECT id, title, ts_rank(search_vector, query) AS rank
   FROM tenders, plainto_tsquery('spanish', $1) query
   WHERE search_vector @@ query
   ORDER BY rank DESC LIMIT $2`,
  searchTerm,   // parameterized — never string-interpolated
  limit,
);
```

### Schema Conventions

```prisma
model Tender {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  title       String
  budget      Decimal  @db.Decimal(18, 2)
  status      TenderStatus @default(DRAFT)
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt
  // Always include createdAt/updatedAt on every model
  // Use cuid() for all PKs (not autoincrement)
}
```

- Field names: **camelCase** in Prisma, **snake_case** in raw SQL
- Always use `@updatedAt` on mutable models
- Soft deletes: `deletedAt DateTime?` + filter `where: { deletedAt: null }`

## RAG / Full-Text Search

- Uses PostgreSQL `tsvector` with Spanish language config
- Index: `search_vector` computed column on `RagChunk`
- Only `$queryRawUnsafe` for SELECT — all parameters positional

## Spring Data JPA (Java backend)

- One repository interface per aggregate root
- JPQL for complex queries; native SQL only for performance-critical paths
- Flyway for all schema changes — **never** use `spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update` in production
- Multi-datasource configured in `application.yml` profiles
- Soft-delete pattern with `@Where(clause = "deleted = false")`

## Do / Don't

- ✅ Always run `prisma generate` after schema changes
- ✅ Index foreign keys and frequently-filtered columns
- ✅ Use Decimal for monetary values (never Float/Double)
- ❌ Never expose Prisma error details to API consumers
- ❌ Never use `deleteMany` without a specific `where` clause
- ❌ Never call `$queryRawUnsafe` with user input via string interpolation
